---
import Base from '~/layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE, STATS, HIGHLIGHTS, COUNTRIES } from '~/data/site';
---
<Base title="About — Odoo Gold Partner" description="Way4Tech is an Odoo Gold Partner with 9+ years of delivery, 500+ deployments, 1000+ custom modules across 18 countries.">
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-ink-900 text-white">
    <div class="absolute inset-0" style="background-image: radial-gradient(circle at 15% 10%, rgba(135,90,123,0.55) 0%, transparent 45%), radial-gradient(circle at 85% 90%, rgba(0,160,157,0.3) 0%, transparent 50%);"></div>
    <div class="container-site relative py-20 sm:py-28">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-white/10 px-4 py-1.5 text-xs font-semibold backdrop-blur">
          <span class="inline-block h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-accent-400"></span> About {SITE.name}
        </div>
        <h1 class="h1 mt-6">Engineers who ship. <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-brand-300 to-accent-300 bg-clip-text text-transparent">Support that stays.</span></h1>
        <p class="lede mt-6 text-ink-200">{SITE.name} is an Odoo Gold Partner specializing exclusively in Odoo. No WordPress. No Shopify. No distractions. Just deep Odoo expertise across 18 countries and 20+ industries.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-site">
      <div class="grid gap-5 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
        {STATS.map(s => (
          <div class="card text-center">
            <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-brand-700">{s.value}</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-ink-600 mt-2">{s.label}</div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-ink-50 border-y border-ink-100">
    <div class="container-site">
      <div class="grid gap-14 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="lg:col-span-2 prose prose-ink max-w-none">
          <h2 class="h3">Our story</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-ink-700">Way4Tech was founded in 2016 with a simple observation: most Odoo partners treat ERP like a one-time project. Configure a few modules, disappear. Six months later you're paying someone else to fix it.</p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-ink-700">We decided to do it differently. We write clean, upgrade-safe code. We support production the same way we built it — with senior engineers, not ticket queues. We stay engaged with our clients for years, not months.</p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-ink-700">Nine years later, we've delivered over 500 go-lives, shipped 1000+ custom modules, and built teams across 18 countries. From 10-person startups to 2000-user enterprises. From Riyadh construction groups to London retail chains.</p>

          <h2 class="h3 mt-12">What we believe</h2>
          <ul class="mt-6 space-y-4">
            <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-brand-600 font-bold mt-1">→</span><div><strong class="text-ink-900">Extend Odoo — don't fight it.</strong><p class="text-ink-600 mt-1">We inherit from Odoo's base models. No parallel universes that break on every upgrade.</p></div></li>
            <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-brand-600 font-bold mt-1">→</span><div><strong class="text-ink-900">Community-first thinking.</strong><p class="text-ink-600 mt-1">Most needs can be met on Odoo Community. We recommend Enterprise only when it genuinely pays off.</p></div></li>
            <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-brand-600 font-bold mt-1">→</span><div><strong class="text-ink-900">Own the outcome.</strong><p class="text-ink-600 mt-1">If something breaks at 2am, that's on us. No finger-pointing.</p></div></li>
            <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-brand-600 font-bold mt-1">→</span><div><strong class="text-ink-900">Compliance baked in.</strong><p class="text-ink-600 mt-1">ZATCA, FBR, GST, MTD, WPS — we ship with compliance, not despite it.</p></div></li>
            <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-brand-600 font-bold mt-1">→</span><div><strong class="text-ink-900">No feature we haven't shipped.</strong><p class="text-ink-600 mt-1">Every module we sell has run in our own operations or a client go-live.</p></div></li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="h3 mt-12">Where we work</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-ink-700">Our engineering team is based in Pakistan with consultants across the UAE, Saudi Arabia, UK, and USA. We deliver remotely with timezone overlap for every region — and on-site for major rollouts.</p>
          <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-2 not-prose">
            {COUNTRIES.map(c => (
              <a href={`/countries/${c.slug}/`} class="chip hover:bg-brand-100 hover:text-brand-800">{c.flag} {c.title}</a>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="lg:col-span-1">
          <div class="sticky top-24 space-y-6">
            <div class="rounded-2xl bg-odoo-gradient p-6 text-white">
              <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold">Odoo Gold Partner</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-brand-100">Certified functional and technical consultants. Covering Odoo v12 through v19.</p>
            </div>
            {HIGHLIGHTS.map(h => (
              <div class="card">
                <div class="text-2xl">{h.icon}</div>
                <h3 class="mt-2 font-semibold">{h.title}</h3>
                <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-ink-600">{h.desc}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-ink-200 bg-white p-6">
              <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold">Get in touch</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-600">Ready to scope a project?</p>
              <a href="/contact/" class="btn-primary w-full mt-5">Contact us</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
